---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<Base
  title="Fretboard — Duditeria"
  description="A personal guitar fretboard tool built quickly with LLMs — visualise scales, modes, and chord shapes across the neck."
  canonical="https://duditeria.com/projects/fretboard"
>
  <!-- Top bar: back nav + title -->
  <header class="top-bar fade-in">
    <a href="/projects" class="back-link">← Projects</a>
    <span class="header-title">Fretboard <span class="header-sub">/ Guitar fretboard visualiser</span></span>
  </header>

  <!-- Section 1: Embedded app -->
  <section class="scene">
    <iframe
      src="https://ekaratzaferis.github.io/fretboard/"
      title="Fretboard app"
      class="embed"
      loading="lazy"
      allowfullscreen
    ></iframe>

    <div class="scene-overlay fade-in">
      <h1 class="title">Fretboard</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Guitar fretboard visualiser</p>
    </div>

    <p class="scroll-hint fade-in-delay-2">scroll ↓</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Description -->
  <section class="content">
    <article>
      <div class="block fade-up">
        <h2>What is it</h2>
        <p>
          A personal guitar fretboard tool I built for myself — to quickly visualise scales,
          modes, and chord shapes across the neck without hunting through tab sites or
          theory books.
        </p>
        <p>
          Not a product. Not polished for an audience. Just a piece of software that
          does exactly what I need, the way I want it, nothing more.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block fade-up">
        <h2>How it was built</h2>
        <p>
          This is an example of what AI-assisted development actually looks like in
          practice — a real use case, a clear mental model, and a few focused prompts.
          The result is a working tool in the time it would have taken to configure
          someone else's app to my liking.
        </p>
        <p>
          No framework sprawl. No dependencies I don't understand. Just the thing I
          needed, built to my taste, owned entirely.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block fade-up">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <ul class="traits">
          <li>Solves a real personal problem — not a demo or toy project</li>
          <li>Built fast with LLMs, but shaped by genuine intent</li>
          <li>A reminder that software can still be personal and small</li>
          <li>You don't need a team or months of work to own your tools</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="block fade-up">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/ekaratzaferis/fretboard"
          class="gh-link"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          View on GitHub →
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  :global(html),
  :global(body) {
    overflow-y: auto !important;
    height: auto !important;
  }

  /* ── Top bar ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .top-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    height: 3rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    background: #000;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .back-link {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: color 0.25s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #ccc;
  }

  .header-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .header-sub {
    color: #444;
  }

  /* ── Section 1: Scene ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .scene {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: calc(100dvh - 3rem);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .embed {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: none;
    display: block;
  }

  .scene-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 5rem;
    left: 2.5rem;
    z-index: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow:
      0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6),
      0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  .tagline {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-indent: 0.42em;
    color: #fff;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  .scroll-hint {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 2rem;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #fff;
    opacity: 0.5;
    pointer-events: none;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  /* ── Section 2: Content ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .content {
    background: #000;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 8rem;
  }

  article {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  .block h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .block p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #b0b0b0;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .block p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  /* Key traits list */
  .traits {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .traits li {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #b0b0b0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .traits li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #333;
  }

  /* GitHub link */
  .gh-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.25rem;
    transition: color 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease;
  }

  .gh-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-color: #444;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .scene-overlay {
      bottom: 5.5rem;
      left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .content {
      padding: 4rem 1.25rem 6rem;
    }
  }
</style>
